                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d393">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">600.127/223: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-08-09T14:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 9, 1921—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 6 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>166. Department’s telegram 115, August 6, 3 p.m. Foreign Office replies in a
                    memorandum dated today <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“The Government of Mexico animated by the same friendly spirit shown by
                            the Washington Government will receive with pleasure the representatives
                            mentioned of the interested companies and will discuss with them the
                            point in question if said companies will communicate to this end with
                            the Department of Hacienda and Public Credit.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Summerlin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
